  "method_notes": [
    "Measurement is downstream of the verdict only: duhem.yml / criteria.md / judge were never edited. Runs used the documented --filter (to isolate an executable criterion, since the full VD aborts) and --no-env-up/--keep-env against one live Crawlab Pro cluster (master+worker over gRPC, real MongoDB) brought up by scripts/up.sh.",
    "Independent re-review signal (T): the task's captured stdout OUTPUT LINE COUNT from Crawlab's own task log (/var/log/crawlab/tasks/<id>/log.txt, framework lines filtered), cross-checked with Mongo tasks.status/error and task_stats.result_count/runtime_duration. The judge reads only the `tasks` collection (status/cmd/spider_id); it never reads output or result_count, so this re-review is genuinely independent.",
    "Crawlab's default FILE log driver puts spider output on disk, not Mongo; result_count (the Mongo yield metric) is structurally 0 for these unconfigured bash spiders. So neither Mongo signal the judge COULD have used would distinguish a real run from a hollow one - the blind spot is intrinsic, not incidental.",
    "in_spec (ground-truth proxy for real work) := task reached terminal `finished` AND error=='' AND output_line_count>=1."
  ],
  "sample_size_caveats": [
    "AC-2 D_hat=0.30 rests on n=25 passes; 95% CI [0.17, 0.46] is wide. To tighten the in-spec proportion CI half-width to +/-0.05 would need ~384 passes (>=~461 runs at this pass rate).",
    "rho values rest on 24-30 judged-true observations per assertion; treat +/-0.1 as the practical uncertainty band.",
    "rho_dynamic has no estimate (single time point); a slope needs repeated runs across future target releases."
  ]
